cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

The paper proposes a learning algorithm for artificial neural networks that is biologically plausible and has connections to predictive coding, a theory in neuroscience. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also compares its proposed algorithms to other biologically-motivated algorithms and evaluates their performance on benchmarks related to computer vision and artificial intelligence, suggesting that it could also fit into the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper's focus on the mechanistic way of describing neurocomputational machinery could also make it relevant to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
